      A <a href="https://www.newmuseum.org/person/spencer-chang/">Y11 NEW INC</a
      > member, their work has been shown in and commissioned by the de Young Museum,
      Gray Area, Hyundai Artlab, and Culturehub. They have co-taught a quarter-long
      courses for SFPC and led workshops for institutions such as Stanford University
      and UPenn. Their work has been featured by publications such as Frieze, MIT
      Technology Review, Rock Paper Shotgun, and Its Nice That.
      <p id="expandingWork"></p>
      <script define:vars={{ workDescription }}>
        let node = createTelescopicTextFromBulletedList(workDescription, {
          textMode: TextMode.Html,
        });
        const container = document.getElementById("expandingWork");
        container.appendChild(node);
      </script>

      <p>
        They are always open to collaborations <span class="italic"
          >(with people or brands)</span
        >, invitations <span class="italic">(to teach or speak)</span>, and
        commissions <span class="italic"
          >(of objects or digital experiences)</span
